hands_on_practices.solution:
1. For a two-body decay $A\to B+C$, the decay width is given by:
$$\Gamma=\frac{|{\cal M}|^2\,p_{\rm cm}}{8\pi\,m_A^2},$$
where $p_{\rm cm}$ is the center-of-mass momentum of the decay products: 
$$p_{\rm cm}=\frac{\sqrt{\lambda(m_A^2,m_B^2,m_C^2)}}{2m_A},\quad \text{with }
\lambda(x,y,z)=x^2+y^2+z^2-2xy-2xz-2yz.$$

2. The ratio of the two decay widths is therefore:
$$R=\frac{\Gamma(a_2^-\to\omega\pi^-)}{\Gamma(a_2^-\to\rho^0\pi^-)}
=\frac{|{\cal M}(a_2^-\to\omega\pi^-)|^2}{|{\cal M}(a_2^-\to\rho^0\pi^-)|^2}
\;\frac{p_{\rm cm}(\text{for }\omega\pi^-)}{p_{\rm cm}(\text{for }\rho^0\pi^-)}.$$

3. Using the given relation for the ratio of the matrix elements:
$$\frac{|\mathcal{M}(a_2^- \to \omega \pi^-)|}{|\mathcal{M}(a_2^- \to \rho^0 \pi^-)|} \approx |\epsilon|
=\left|\frac{\delta m^2}{m_\omega^2-m_\rho^2}\right|,$$
and the expression for the momenta, we get:
$$R
\approx \epsilon^2\,
\frac{\sqrt{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\omega^2,m_\pi^2)}/(2m_{a_2})}
{\sqrt{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\rho^2,m_\pi^2)}/(2m_{a_2})}
=\epsilon^2\,
\sqrt{\frac{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\omega^2,m_\pi^2)}
{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\rho^2,m_\pi^2)}}.$$

4. Substituting the expression for $\epsilon$:
$$R
=\frac{(\delta m^2)^2}{(m_\omega^2-m_\rho^2)^2}
\sqrt{\frac{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\omega^2,m_\pi^2)}
{\lambda(m_{a_2}^2,m_\rho^2,m_\pi^2)}}.$$
